title: Anne of Green Gables (version 2)
creator: Lucy Maud Montgomery
description: Librivox recording of Anne of Green Gables by Lucy Maud Montgomery. Read by rachelellen Lucy Maud Montgomery's classic children's novel, Anne of Green Gables tells the story of a red headed orphan girl with a personality you can't help but love. Despite her "tragical" past, Anne's optimism and imagination have helped her to always see the best in things. Anne's life changes considerably when she is accidentally adopted by the Cuthberts, a brother and sister who thought they were getting a boy to help out on the farm. The Cuthberts decide Anne will have to be sent back to the orphange but before they know it, she has begun to work her way into their hearts. (Summary by Annie Coleman) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audiobooks, or to become a volunteer reader, please visit librivox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; montgomery; green gables
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
I popped in an mp3 cd of rachelellen reading Anne of Green Gables to entertain my family as we had a long drive this Thanksgiving weekend. I have been trying to introduce my husband to the wonders of audiobooks (if for no other reason than to get to listen to them on family car trips) but he was never much interested. 

Rachelellen's reading is wonderful. Both my husband and six year old son were entranced and we my husband was fast forwarding through the intro's of the chapters to get to the reading at the end of the book because he wanted to finish it before our trip was over and time was running short.

Excellent reading. You can tell that the reader loves this book.

An entancing book, beautifully read
As a 63 year old man I do not think that I would have been amongst the book's intended audience. I downloaded the MP3s to give to my great niece, who is 8, but found myself listening to the whole book! 
I now have all of the Anne of Green Gables books, and hope tht Bethany likes them.

This is a terrific reading of a wonderful story! Anne of Green Gables is billed as a children's book, but really, it can be enjoyed by anyone who needs a little enthusiasm, positivity, and sheer joy in their lives. I can't believe I'm just "discovering" these novels now -- at the tender age of 35!
